# Program Design Document

## Program Name

Assigmnet 1.5 calculator 

## Purpose

This program does basic calculations with any integer and 5 basic operations but does not compute numbers being divided or moduloed with 0. 

---

## Inputs

List all inputs the program will receive.

Example:

* "First digits"
* "Second Digits"
* "symbol of operation" 

---

## Outputs

List what the program will display or produce.


Final calucation.
Error message when dividing or using modulo by 0. 

---

## Variables

| Variable | Type   | Purpose                   |
| -------- | ------ | ------------------------- |
| A    | int | Stores test score         |
| B  | int | inputs/stores number |
| Operation    | char   | order of operation based on chosen symbol      |

---

## Key Design Choices

I used an if statement to handle the error message when diving by 0 and did switch statement because there are multiple operations.


---

## Program Steps (Algorithm)

1. Get input from the user, integers a and b asking the user for the first and second digit. 
2. asks user to choose order of operation symbol. 
3. Perform calculations.
4. use switch and if statement to check for order of operation based on symbol and check wether user is diving by 0 in which an error message will be displayed. 
5. Display output of final calculations. 

